<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_LiveMode_Skills" s="314255">
  <T n="name">0x1EC27FE6<!--String: "Skills"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_Skills_1.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:14de2a0bead2c510</T>
      <T n="text">0xB1759084<!--String: "Sims can develop a multitude of different <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills</font></b>! Why not try out Gardening, Mischief, Photography, Violin, Programming, or Fitness, just to mention a few!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_Skills_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:14de2a0bead2c513</T>
      <T n="text">0xE4175B13<!--String: "Skills give your Sim all sorts of <b><font color='#199C2C'>benefits</font></b>. For example, Cooking produces tasty meals that will make them happy, Charisma gives them a boost to relationships, and Painting a masterpiece can earn some big Simoleons!\n\nSkills are also essential to getting to the higher levels of a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Career</font></b>. Once your Sim has joined a Career, you can see any <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skill requirements</font></b> in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Career panel</font></b>. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_Skills_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:14de2a0bead2c512</T>
      <T n="text">0x456BE54E<!--String: "Practice makes perfect! Interact with special <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skill Objects</font></b> or other Sims to raise <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skill levels</font></b>. If your Sim is Happy, or is in the Skill’s associated Emotion, they will raise it faster.\n\nWhen they’re building a Skill, the <b><font color='#199C2C'>bar</font></b> over your Sim’s head shows you their <b><font color='#199C2C'>progress</font></b> towards the next Skill level. You can also keep track of your Sim’s Skills in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skill panel</font></b>.\n\nFor more information about specific Skills, check out the Lessons in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills</font></b> section of the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Live Mode category</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
